# LILT — parser and masking

When editing parser or placeholder code, preserve structural integrity of LaTeX.
Canonical guide: [docs/architecture/03-parser-masking.md](docs/architecture/03-parser-masking.md).

## MUST

- Use AST-based parsing (`pylatexenc`) with gap-preserving roundtrip verification.
- Keep opaque / transparent / deep-traversal taxonomy consistent with L1.
- Treat `placeholder_contract.py` as the single source of truth for placeholder regex and validation.
- Persist placeholder maps at sync; build unmasks from TM maps, not ad-hoc rewrites.
- Multiset-exact placeholder matching before accepting translations.

## NEVER

- Replace structural parsing with regex-only segmentation of whole documents.
- “Simplify” unmasking by dropping tags, renaming prefixes, or inventing new placeholder shapes without updating the contract + validators + L1 guide.
- Send raw math, verbatim, `\ref`/`\cite`, or opaque environments to the LLM unmasked.
- Break roundtrip: reconstructed bytes from parse blocks must match source for covered spans.

## Tests

Prefer extending existing parser/placeholder tests. Do not add third-party paper corpora into this repository.
